  "description": "Something depletes your motivation, leaving you struggling to find the energy to act.",
  "content": "The exhaustion isn't just physical—it's existential. Every task feels pointless, every effort seems futile. You've been pushing for so long, and what do you have to show for it? The momentum you'd been riding suddenly evaporates. Your to-do list becomes a monument to obligations you can't bring yourself to care about. People ask what's wrong, but you don't have words for it. You're just... done.",
