      "id": "collapse_into_rest",
      "text": "Stop fighting and just rest",
      "description": "Maybe your body is forcing what your mind wouldn't allow.",
      "resultText": "You let go. Cancel commitments. Ignore the guilt. Sleep for hours. Stare at walls. Do nothing and try not to judge yourself for it. It feels like failure, like giving up, but it also feels necessary. You're so tired. Maybe this isn't depression or laziness—maybe it's just the inevitable consequence of pushing too hard for too long. Maybe rest is exactly what you need.",
